                            <comment id="13135139" author="uiterlix" created="Tue, 25 Oct 2011 15:22:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See attached testcase for reproduction of the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13135140" author="uiterlix" created="Tue, 25 Oct 2011 15:23:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The testcase also finishes with a warning which needs to be checked:&lt;br/&gt;
WARNING: Invocation of &apos;added&apos; failed. (java.lang.IllegalStateException: Can only register services while bundle is active or activating.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13178448" author="uiterlix" created="Mon, 2 Jan 2012 16:35:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Find the enclosed patch which resolves the issue. It also adds the possibility to provide a swap callback method for an adapter service which is called when the service the adapter adapts is changed due to an aspect becoming (un)available. The modified adapter tests are also included in a separate patch file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13178520" author="marrs" created="Mon, 2 Jan 2012 19:23:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for this extensive patch, Xander. As you can see from the commit log, I applied the patches with some changes, so it probably makes sense that you review my changes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
